<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Wizards can't sustain their damage output in fights that last longer than those that existed before Velious. This is the issue you're heading at. And, sure, giving Wizards a larger mana pool or a form of massive mana regeneration would fix it. But it also makes them more efficient in all other forms of casting. To 'balance' that out, we'd have to increase the mana cost on all non-damage wizards spells. <P>I'd rather find a more specific solution. And the bane spells are a good solution. <BR>______________this is what they said.....<P><BR>this is what i say as a non wizard.... Is it ok to give melee more and more and more and more to make them that much better compared to when velious came out? and on top of that you can go out get that gear and give to your level one. Now what you have is a melee at one that is non killable, compare it to a velious equipment equipped wizard, does the wizard do any better damage? No. Can the wizard die as fast as he used to? Yes. Verant, jeez. not even worth the effort to complain about their "idea" of balanced. and the remark about the bane line is a crock, does that help out the middle level guys any?<BR>/rude verant.
</FONT>
