<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Here are some suggestions to help out the wizards and other caster classes. Fist of all I think that most of the classes are rather balanced till you hit Kunark and Velios at that point melee classes take over. I do think that the wizard class needs help from the teens up. I have played a wizard from 0-33 and a SK from 0-33 I also have a bard and a cleric out of there teens. I personally think that the wizard has two main faults one is no group buffs and two we are resisted and are only effective against blue and some yellow mobs. Most good groups that I have wanted to join are attacking reds. If this is the case I will not group with them cause I know that I will not be able to hit the mobs with my spells.  Mana regen is an issue for all casters so I don&#8217;t consider it to be a balance problem. The wizards have very few spells that last more then an instant and I think that&#8217;s the way it should be. When we burn let us burn bright.<P>Solutions:<BR>All casters<BR>1.	Less resist around the board (almost all classes have spells that deal with fire, Ice and magic make it so if you use the correct spell against a mob they will not resist them. Hit a fire imp with a cold spell will not resist the spell. Hit a fire imp with fire and it will resist)<P>Wizards<BR>1.	Refer all casters solutions. This will greatly aid the wizards because they have a wider rage of spells of each type.  (Fire, Cold and Magic) a mage may need to reach back a few levels to find a cold-based spell to hit the imp. A wizard will only have to go back one level.<BR>2.	TAUNT the main reason you don&#8217;t see a wizard pull their wait in a battle is because they can&#8217;t without killing themselves. If my 33 level wizard casts any of her 33 level spells before the mob is less than 1/3 of its life I will be killed. I don&#8217;t think it should be this way. I think wizard spells should come with less agro then other casters allowing us to deal the damage without getting attacked. So I can throw that nuke in at 2/3 life and then get another in at 1/3 without the mob killing me. That would allow me to dish out 518 points of dam in two blasts that&#8217;s not bad. It does allot better them what I&#8217;m doing now. <P>Ok let me head this off at the pass. Why should wizard spells have less agro then other casters? It really does not sound fair. Well it is all we wizards can do. Most other casters have buffs, dots or pets that can do allot of damage over time. Most of these spells are mana efficient and can be cast at the start of a battle allowing the caster to sit down and med while they work. The only thing that a wizard can to is nuke. If we can&#8217;t blast but once per battle we are almost useless to a group. Allow us to throw off two nuke at our level let them not get resisted and let us not die. Right now I can&#8217;t do that. Am I asking to much?<P>My two copper<BR>Liloth Impbane 33-wiz<BR>Mirtai 33-SK<BR>Ambyr 20-bard
</FONT>
