Greetings all ...!<P>Hail Grimstaff ..! <P>Take heed:<BR>lvl 50 Warrior (<I>pre-kunark</I>) was duel weilding Short Swords of Ykesha (8/24, ratio .708) That proced and stunned...!  <P>lvl 50 Wizard (<I>pre-Kunark</I>) had Ice Comet spell (1120 dmg  for 400 mana, ratio 2.8)<P><BR>Forward to today:<P>lvl 50 Warrior (<I>velious</I>) weilding <B>Wurmslayer</B>(2500pp) (25/40, ratio 1.27) and a <B>Green Jade Broad Sword</B>(12k) (11/25, ratio .920)<P>COMPARE:<BR>Primary hand- was .708, now 1.27 = <B>75%</B> more damage<BR>Secondary hand- was .708, now .920 = <B>29%</B> more damage<BR>Added together thats 104% more damage (<B>over double than before</B>)<BR>Then you add in the fact that 80% of all Warriors have an <B>FBSS</B> (18% haste) or better makes those <B>%</B> go up.<P><BR>Lvl 50 Wizard (<I>velious</I>)weilding his best spell Ice Comet, 1120 dmg for 400 mana. With possable 200 to 300 more mana due to <I>Velious</I> armor/eqipment.<BR>% of Damage increase= <B>0%</B><BR>% of Damage efficiency = <B>0%</B><BR>% of Total damage= <B>10%</B> due to extra mana.<P>Now, there is not added benifit of a FBSS for wizards that increase the efficiency of our spells, and Clarity is nothing more than a heal for a Warrior(he cant fight without health=Wizards can't fight without mana).  There is no new magical device that allows us to take 5-20% less damage (meaning the new Velious UBER high AC items; allowing Warriors to take less damage)<P>Clarity is nice... but it is not the <I>DEFINNING</I> characteristic Wizards are looking for.  All this mis-spent energy comming up with wacky idea for wizards...!  Here is the answere... Grimstaff, Sylvain, Nickobolis, ETC had the answere 14 month ago...!<P><B>Mana Efficincy ...!</B><P>It is a extremely simple solution, that is EXTREMLY tailorable to any condition...!<P>Want a Wizard to feel apart of battle, but only do slightly more damage than before...?<P><B>Torrent</B> (lvl 50)<BR>Damage: 1000<BR>mana: 200<BR>Casting time: 1.0 seconds<BR>hold-back: 2.3 (standard)<BR>Re-cast: 60 seconds<BR>Look at this spell closly.. the efficiency is spectaculiar... but when played out. you only end up casting it once per fight!<P><B>Wrath</B> (lvl 54)<BR>Damage: 2000 x unlimited (PB)<BR>mana: 100<BR>Casting time: 0.5<BR>Re-cast: 40 min<BR>Spell does exactly what is it named... a wizard is pressured and getting beat on (or in a situation that is mounting his anger) he cringes and lets loose his WRATH. with a 40 minutes re-cast time, this spell will only be memed in situation were it will be needed...!  perhaps meding in Iclade and getting jumping by a few whirling dervishes, and a few more get on you...!  finally you caint take enough of the greenies...! FELL MY WRATH. (aye, you could just root, root, root, root the forth one, then walk away, or just AE or Nuke them.  But your a lvl 54 Wizard.<P><B>Solar Strike</B>(lvl 60) my version of Sunstrike<BR>Damage: 1650<BR>Mana: 370<BR>Casting time: 4.0<BR>re-cast: 15 second<BR>More efficiency, but less damage over time.. due to the longer re-cast. Not a chain spell.<P><B>Vexing Rage</B>(lvl 44)<BR>Damage: 175<BR>Mana: 45<BR>Casting time: 0.5<BR>re-cast: 15 seconds<BR>Efficient run stopper (cause EVERY wizard overkills the runners, wasting precious mana).<P>These spells might sound uber, but put them into a fight, you caint have all of them memed, but it gives us some better choices when meming our spells per group.<P>Also, a FWSS (Flowing White Silk Sash) thats adds 18% more damage to our spells woulds also be cool ...!<P>--------------------<P>--------------------------------<P>-Burabis, the un-guildable...!
